dcterms:creator: D. Krajzewicz
J. Erdmann
M. Behrisch
L. Bieker
dcterms:description: SUMO is a traffic simulation software that allows for the modeling of urban mobility and traffic flow, providing a platform for testing various traffic control algorithms.
dcterms:title: SUMO (Simulation of Urban MObility)

dcterms:creator: P. Varaiya
dcterms:description: Max Pressure (MP) Control is a traffic signal control strategy that optimizes the flow of traffic at signalized intersections by prioritizing movements based on queue lengths.
dcterms:title: Max Pressure (MP) Control

dcterms:description: Traffic Demand Data generated with Poisson distribution is used to simulate vehicle arrivals at intersections for testing traffic control algorithms.
dcterms:title: Traffic Demand Data (generated with Poisson distribution)

dcterms:description: Trip Generating Probabilities are used to model the likelihood of trips between origin-destination pairs in traffic simulations.
dcterms:title: Trip Generating Probabilities

dcterms:description: Traffic Signal Control Data includes information on the timing and operation of traffic signals used in the simulation environment.
dcterms:title: Traffic Signal Control Data
